{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-18",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_18_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Fall Guy",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 6,
  "page_total": 8,
  "page_start_sec": 1231.86,
  "page_end_sec": 1479.5,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.553,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 1231.86,
      "end": 1232.3,
      "text": "Now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1232.32,
      "end": 1232.54,
      "text": "now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1232.6,
      "end": 1233.04,
      "text": "Wilmer,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1233.2,
      "end": 1233.7,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1233.98,
      "end": 1235.34,
      "text": "we can't have any of that."
    },
    {
      "start": 1236.16,
      "end": 1238.84,
      "text": "You shouldn't let yourself attach so much importance to these"
    },
    {
      "start": 1238.96,
      "end": 1239.12,
      "text": "things."
    },
    {
      "start": 1239.5,
      "end": 1240.1,
      "text": "You..."
    },
    {
      "start": 1240.84,
      "end": 1241.18,
      "text": "The boy,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1241.32,
      "end": 1243.02,
      "text": "not taking his eyes from Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1243.12,
      "end": 1245.36,
      "text": "spoke in a choked voice out the side of"
    },
    {
      "start": 1245.36,
      "end": 1245.76,
      "text": "his mouth."
    },
    {
      "start": 1246.688,
      "end": 1248.3,
      "text": "Make him lay off me then."
    },
    {
      "start": 1249.66,
      "end": 1252.0,
      "text": "I'm going to fog him if he keeps it up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1252.1,
      "end": 1252.9,
      "text": "and there won't be"
    },
    {
      "start": 1253.0,
      "end": 1254.96,
      "text": "anything that'll stop me from doing it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1255.5,
      "end": 1256.06,
      "text": "Now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1256.06,
      "end": 1256.62,
      "text": "Wilmer,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1256.84,
      "end": 1258.78,
      "text": "Gutman said and turned to Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 1259.44,
      "end": 1259.84,
      "text": "His face"
    },
    {
      "start": 1260.04,
      "end": 1261.7,
      "text": "and voice were under control now."
    },
    {
      "start": 1262.6,
      "end": 1263.36,
      "text": "Your plan is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1263.46,
      "end": 1263.9,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1264.14,
      "end": 1265.6,
      "text": "as I said in the first place,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1265.82,
      "end": 1266.52,
      "text": "not at all"
    },
    {
      "start": 1266.58,
      "end": 1266.92,
      "text": "practical."
    },
    {
      "start": 1267.33,
      "end": 1269.8,
      "text": "Let's not say anything more about it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1270.72,
      "end": 1272.54,
      "text": "Spade looked from one of them to the other.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1273.02,
      "end": 1274.06,
      "text": "He had stopped smiling."
    },
    {
      "start": 1274.78,
      "end": 1276.6,
      "text": "His face held no expression at all."
    },
    {
      "start": 1276.86,
      "end": 1278.52,
      "text": "I say what I please,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1278.84,
      "end": 1279.58,
      "text": "he told them."
    },
    {
      "start": 1280.32,
      "end": 1281.14,
      "text": "You certainly do,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1281.36,
      "end": 1282.26,
      "text": "Gutman said quickly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1282.82,
      "end": 1285.42,
      "text": "and that's one of the things I've always admired in you."
    },
    {
      "start": 1285.86,
      "end": 1287.18,
      "text": "But this matter is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1287.34,
      "end": 1287.96,
      "text": "as I say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1288.12,
      "end": 1289.24,
      "text": "not at all practical,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1289.88,
      "end": 1293.46,
      "text": "so there's not the least bit of use of discussing it any further,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1293.62,
      "end": 1295.06,
      "text": "as you can see for yourself."
    },
    {
      "start": 1295.81,
      "end": 1297.44,
      "text": "I can't see it for myself,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1297.72,
      "end": 1298.26,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1298.66,
      "end": 1300.14,
      "text": "and you haven't made me see it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1300.2,
      "end": 1301.5,
      "text": "and I don't think you can."
    },
    {
      "start": 1302.36,
      "end": 1303.34,
      "text": "He frowned at Gutman."
    },
    {
      "start": 1304.288,
      "end": 1305.12,
      "text": "Let's get this straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 1306.02,
      "end": 1308.14,
      "text": "Am I wasting time talking to you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1308.5,
      "end": 1310.18,
      "text": "I thought this was your show."
    },
    {
      "start": 1311.14,
      "end": 1312.66,
      "text": "Should I do my talking to the punk?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1313.5,
      "end": 1314.56,
      "text": "I know how to do that."
    },
    {
      "start": 1315.24,
      "end": 1319.2,
      "text": "\"No, sir,\" Gutman replied, \"you're quite right in dealing with me.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1319.2,
      "end": 1321.44,
      "text": "Spade said: \"All right.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1321.44,
      "end": 1323.62,
      "text": "Now I've got another suggestion."
    },
    {
      "start": 1323.62,
      "end": 1325.62,
      "text": "It's not as good as the first,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1325.62,
      "end": 1327.04,
      "text": "but it's better than nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 1327.04,
      "end": 1328.26,
      "text": "Want to hear it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1329.18,
      "end": 1330.1,
      "text": "\"Most assuredly.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1330.34,
      "end": 1331.66,
      "text": "\"Give them Cairo.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1332.58,
      "end": 1335.68,
      "text": "Cairo hastily picked up his pistol from the table beside him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1335.9,
      "end": 1338.42,
      "text": "He held it tight in his lap with both hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1338.76,
      "end": 1341.8,
      "text": "its muzzle pointed at the floor a little to one side"
    },
    {
      "start": 1341.8,
      "end": 1342.44,
      "text": "of the sofa."
    },
    {
      "start": 1342.7,
      "end": 1345.14,
      "text": "His face had become yellowish again."
    },
    {
      "start": 1345.6,
      "end": 1348.7,
      "text": "His black eyes darted their gaze from face to"
    },
    {
      "start": 1348.7,
      "end": 1348.98,
      "text": "face."
    },
    {
      "start": 1349.8,
      "end": 1352.06,
      "text": "The opaqueness of his eyes made them seem flat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1352.26,
      "end": 1352.84,
      "text": "two-dimensional."
    },
    {
      "start": 1353.57,
      "end": 1354.22,
      "text": "Gutman,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1354.38,
      "end": 1355.18,
      "text": "looking as if he"
    },
    {
      "start": 1355.18,
      "end": 1357.38,
      "text": "could not believe he had heard what he had heard,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1357.52,
      "end": 1358.08,
      "text": "asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1358.66,
      "end": 1359.14,
      "text": "Do what?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1360.12,
      "end": 1361.26,
      "text": "\"Give the police Cairo.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1361.48,
      "end": 1361.58,
      "text": "Gutman seemed about to laugh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1362.56,
      "end": 1363.78,
      "text": "seemed about to laugh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1364.0,
      "end": 1364.82,
      "text": "but he did not laugh."
    },
    {
      "start": 1365.1,
      "end": 1365.88,
      "text": "Finally,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1365.9,
      "end": 1366.76,
      "text": "he exclaimed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1366.9,
      "end": 1367.48,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1367.54,
      "end": 1368.0,
      "text": "by Gad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1368.08,
      "end": 1368.34,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1368.76,
      "end": 1369.9,
      "text": "in an uncertain tone."
    },
    {
      "start": 1370.84,
      "end": 1372.42,
      "text": "It's not as good as giving them the punk,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1372.92,
      "end": 1373.26,
      "text": "Spade said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1374.112,
      "end": 1375.06,
      "text": "Cairo's not a gunman"
    },
    {
      "start": 1375.06,
      "end": 1378.36,
      "text": "and he carries a smaller gun than Thursby and Jacobi were shot with."
    },
    {
      "start": 1379.28,
      "end": 1380.08,
      "text": "We'll have to go to more"
    },
    {
      "start": 1380.16,
      "end": 1381.1,
      "text": "trouble framing him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1381.64,
      "end": 1383.64,
      "text": "but that's better than not giving the police anybody."
    },
    {
      "start": 1384.8,
      "end": 1385.88,
      "text": "Cairo cried in a voice shrill with indignation.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1387.872,
      "end": 1388.86,
      "text": "Suppose we give them you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1389.0,
      "end": 1389.26,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1389.32,
      "end": 1389.72,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1389.76,
      "end": 1390.75,
      "text": "or Miss O'Shaughnessy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1391.56,
      "end": 1392.2,
      "text": "How about that"
    },
    {
      "start": 1392.32,
      "end": 1394.24,
      "text": "if you're so set on giving them somebody?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1394.924,
      "end": 1398.164,
      "text": "Spade smiled at the Levantine and answered him evenly:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1398.164,
      "end": 1401.584,
      "text": "\"You people want the falcon. I've got it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1401.584,
      "end": 1404.104,
      "text": "A fall-guy is part of the price I'm asking."
    },
    {
      "start": 1404.104,
      "end": 1405.244,
      "text": "As for Miss O'Shaughnessy—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1405.904,
      "end": 1411.324,
      "text": "his dispassionate glance moved to her white perplexed face and then back to Cairo"
    },
    {
      "start": 1411.324,
      "end": 1414.224,
      "text": "and his shoulders rose and fell a fraction of an inch"
    },
    {
      "start": 1414.224,
      "end": 1417.004,
      "text": "if you think she can be rigged for the part"
    },
    {
      "start": 1417.004,
      "end": 1419.464,
      "text": "I'm perfectly willing to discuss it with you."
    },
    {
      "start": 1420.34,
      "end": 1422.96,
      "text": "The girl put her hands to her throat,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1423.3,
      "end": 1425.5,
      "text": "uttered a short strangled cry, and moved farther away from him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1425.92,
      "end": 1426.8,
      "text": "Cairo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1426.94,
      "end": 1428.88,
      "text": "his face and body twitching with excitement,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1429.34,
      "end": 1429.78,
      "text": "exclaimed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1429.95,
      "end": 1432.12,
      "text": "You seem to forget that you are not"
    },
    {
      "start": 1432.12,
      "end": 1433.9,
      "text": "in a position to insist on anything."
    },
    {
      "start": 1434.944,
      "end": 1436.0,
      "text": "Spade laughed, a harsh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1436.12,
      "end": 1436.98,
      "text": "derisive snort."
    },
    {
      "start": 1438.048,
      "end": 1440.48,
      "text": "Gutman said in a voice that tried to make firmness ingratiating:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1442.24,
      "end": 1442.58,
      "text": "Come now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1442.62,
      "end": 1442.92,
      "text": "gentlemen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1443.1,
      "end": 1445.42,
      "text": "let's keep our discussion on a friendly basis."
    },
    {
      "start": 1446.56,
      "end": 1447.6,
      "text": "But there certainly is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1447.72,
      "end": 1449.22,
      "text": "he was addressing Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1449.41,
      "end": 1450.76,
      "text": "something in what Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1450.84,
      "end": 1451.44,
      "text": "Cairo says."
    },
    {
      "start": 1451.82,
      "end": 1454.14,
      "text": "You must take into consideration the—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1454.14,
      "end": 1459.68,
      "text": "\"Like hell I must.\" Spade flung his words out with a brutal sort of carelessness",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1459.68,
      "end": 1463.96,
      "text": "that gave them more weight than they could have got from dramatic emphasis"
    },
    {
      "start": 1463.96,
      "end": 1465.34,
      "text": "or from loudness."
    },
    {
      "start": 1465.34,
      "end": 1468.74,
      "text": "\"If you kill me, how are you going to get the bird?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1468.74,
      "end": 1472.82,
      "text": "If I know you can't afford to kill me till you have it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1472.82,
      "end": 1474.8,
      "text": "how are you going to scare me into giving it to you?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1474.58,
      "end": 1477.92,
      "text": "Gutman cocked his head to the left and considered these questions.",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}